@434@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@434@^http://www.steeda.com/ford-racing-gt500-mustang-high-capacity-oil-pan-161-m-6675-msvt/^@^Steeda^@^Ford Racing GT500 Mustang High Capacity Oil Pan (07-14 GT500)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/2/161-m-6675-msvt.jpg^@^161-M-6675-MSVT^@^<p>Designed and engineered by Ford Motor Company for the 662hp 2013 GT500 this oil pan will retrofit to all previous 2007-2012 GT500 models. </p> <p>Featuring lightweight cast aluminum construction and an 8.5 quart oil capacity. This oil pan also includes a combination oil pan gasket windage tray and crank scraper assembly. Also includes pickup tube and pan attachment bolts. </p> <p><strong>Product Benefits</strong> </p> <ul> <li>Upgraded Oil Pan designed by Ford for your GT500</li> <li>Direct fit replacement</li> <li>Includes gasket windage tray crank scraper and hardware</li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 5 Hours</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Tech Recommended</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Shop Tools</strong></p><p>Model year(s): <strong>2014 2013 2012 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007</strong></p><p>Model(s): <strong>GT500</strong></p><p>Transmission(s): <strong>Manual</strong></p>^@^Mustang^@^ GT500 ^@^Mustang Engine^@^2014 2013 2012 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007 ^@^Mustang Engine Pans^@^9.95^
@435@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@435@^http://www.steeda.com/moroso-aluminum-mustang-oil-pan-369-20572/^@^Steeda^@^Moroso Aluminum Mustang Oil Pan (11-14)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/2/369-20572.jpg^@^369-20572^@^<p>This fabricated Aluminum Moroso Race Oil Pan holds 2 more quarts than stock and is designed to be used with the factory windage tray oil pump pickup and dipstick making it perfect for race applications. </p> <p>Fabricated from aluminum this Moroso Oil Pan has a thick rail with a 2-3/8&quot; deep front section and a 6-5/8&quot; deep by 9-1/8&quot; long rear sump and features a race-proven trap door assembly and anti-slosh baffle that keeps oil contained in the oil pump pickup area. </p> <p>This Moroso 10 quart Race Oil Pan is designed for Drag and Road Race applications on the 2011 to 2013 GT Mustangs equipped with a 5.0L Four-Valve Coyote V8 engine and simply bolts in place of the stock one. </p> <p><strong>Product Benefits</strong> </p> <ul> <li>Holds two more quarts than stock</li> <li>1/2' NPT fitting for supercharger drain back</li> <li>1/2&quot; NPT fitting for oil temperature sensor</li> <li>20mm fitting for the factory oil level sensor</li> <li>Finished is clear zinc fully fabricated</li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 3 1/2 Hours</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Tech Recommended</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Basic Tools</strong></p><p>Model year(s): <strong>2014 2013 2012 2011</strong></p><p>Model(s): <strong>GT GT500 Boss</strong></p><p>Transmission(s): <strong>Manual Automatic</strong></p>^@^Mustang^@^ GT GT500 Boss ^@^Mustang Engine^@^2014 2013 2012 2011 ^@^Mustang Engine Pans^@^544.95^
@436@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@436@^http://www.steeda.com/steeda-black-billet-mustang-oil-separator-79-14-555-3713-b/^@^Steeda^@^Steeda Black Billet Mustang Oil Separator (79-14)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/7/steeda-black-billet-mustang-oil-separator-79-15-555-3713-b.jpg; http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/7/steeda-black-billet-mustang-oil-separator-79-15-555-3713-b(2).jpg^@^555-3713-B^@^<p>Our oil separator is crafted from aerospace grade billet aluminum for light weight and great looks. Connects to PCV hose to prevent oil and crankcase vapors from getting into the intake manifold and decreasing your fuel octane. </p> <p>Fully sealed to ensure no vacuum leaks and simple to service. Holds up to three ounces of fluid for service intervals lapsing each oil change. </p> <p>Looks great and matches with the rest of our line of underhood dress up items. </p> <p>Includes hardware for installation. </p> <p><strong>Product Benefits</strong> </p> <ul> <li>Fits any car with a 3/8&quot; or 1/2&quot; vacuum system</li> <li>Lightweight Aerospace Grade Aluminum</li> <li>Matches Steeda's line-up of bling caps</li> <li>Simple to service</li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 30 Minutes</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Easy Install</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Basic Tools</span> </div> </div> <div style=with:100%

