@1217@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@1217@^http://www.steeda.com/edelbrock-mustang-intake-manifold-125-3821/^@^Steeda^@^Edelbrock Performer 5.0 Mustang Intake Manifold (86-95)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/2/125-3821.jpg; http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/2/125-3821-1.jpg^@^125-3821^@^<p>Edelbrock's intake can free up 8-12 horsepower on a stock 5.0 and up to 30 horsepower on an engine with performance cylinder heads! Edelbrock really does their homework. These manifolds feature the best air distribution (most even air flow from cylinder to cylinder) of any manifold we've seen. The removable plenum cover gives you direct access to the intake runners for easy porting and polishing. </p> <p>The Performer 5.0 is your choice for most daily-driven street cars which need a lot of mid-range torque and horsepower below 6000 rpm. </p> <p>The Performer RPM is perfect for high rpm when combined with a rev-extender. The Performer RPM's shorter runners are also a great match for the high airflow needs of stroker motors and 351 conversions. </p><p>Time to install: <strong>About 12 Hours</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Tech Required</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Shop Tools</strong></p><p>Model year(s): <strong>1995 1994 1993 1992 1991 1990 1989 1988 1987 1986</strong></p><p>Model(s): <strong>5.0L V8 Cobra GT</strong></p><p>Transmission(s): <strong>Manual Automatic</strong></p>^@^Mustang^@^ 5.0L V8 Cobra GT ^@^Mustang Induction^@^1995 1994 1993 1992 1991 1990 1989 1988 1987 1986 ^@^Mustang Manifolds^@^33.95^
@1222@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@1222@^http://www.steeda.com/edelbrock-mustang-70mm-throttle-body-125-3845/^@^Steeda^@^Edelbrock Mustang 70mm Throttle Body (94-95 GT)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/2/125-3845.jpg^@^125-3845^@^<p>More air = More horsepower! These high flow throttle bodies flow significantly more air than their stock counterparts increasing top-end horsepower. A-must-have for serious performance when using upgraded intake manifolds and cylinder heads. </p> <p><strong>Product Benefits</strong> </p> <ul> <li>Increased horsepower and torque </li> <li>Improved throttle response </li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 30 Minutes</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Easy</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Basic Tools</span> </div> </div> <div style=with:100%

