>Product Benefits</strong> </p> <ul> <li>Better handling more stable cornering</li> <li>Light weight</li> <li>QA1 quality</li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 3 Hours</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Tech Recommended</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Basic Tools</strong></p><p>Model year(s): <strong>1993 1992 1991 1990 1989 1988 1987 1986 1985 1984 1983 1982 1981 1980 1979</strong></p><p>Model(s): <strong>5.0L V8 Cobra V6 2.3L</strong></p><p>Transmission(s): <strong>Manual Automatic</strong></p>^@^Mustang^@^ 5.0L V8 Cobra V6 2.3L ^@^Mustang Suspension^@^1993 1992 1991 1990 1989 1988 1987 1986 1985 1984 1983 1982 1981 1980 1979 ^@^Mustang Control Arms^@^389.95^
@1295@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@1295@^http://www.steeda.com/qa1-adjustable-mustang-shocks-and-struts-05-10-338-hs605s/^@^Steeda^@^QA1 Adjustable Mustang Shocks & Struts (05-10)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/530/detailed/5/qa1-adjustable-mustang-shocks-and-struts-05-10-338-hs605s.jpg^@^338-HS605S^@^<p>QA1 Aluminum Body Struts are 3 lbs. lighter (each) than any other strut available precision-machined for perfect piston bore fit black hard anodized inside and out for incredible strength and durability fully threaded for easy coil-over conversion. </p> <p>QA1 struts feature exceptional piston pod design. QA1's piston rod goes completely through the body and is supported on both ends for greater strength and more consistent valving. Piston rod bind is eliminated. </p> <p>Externally adjustable valving is easily adjustable on both shocks and struts. Changes are accomplished from under the hood for easy access. One knob allows for quick and precise valving changes from street to strip to road racing. </p> <p>Large body mono-tube shock design provide for the use of a larger piston and greater fluid volume. More fluid means lower temperatures and the larger piston allows for greater fluid control for more consistent valving. </p> <p>Struts and shocks are an easy bolt-in installation and are a direct replacement for the factory components. They can be used in conjunction with stock or aftermarket K-members. For 2005+ Mustang applications a QA1 or Steeda strut mount is required. </p> <p><strong>Note: </strong>For coil over use part number 338-MU1CCM coil over kit is required. These struts are re-valveable and re-buildable by QA1 Authorized Service Centers. </p> <p><strong> Product Benefits</strong> </p> <ul> <li>Enough adjustability for your combination</li> <li>3 lbs lighter than per strut the next lightest competitor</li> <li>Removeable sway bar mounting tabs</li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 4 Hours</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Tech Recommended</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Shop Tools</strong></p><p>Model year(s): <strong>2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005</strong></p><p>Model(s): <strong>Bullitt GT V6</strong></p><p>Transmission(s): <strong>Manual Automatic</strong></p>^@^Mustang^@^ Bullitt GT V6 ^@^Mustang Suspension^@^2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005 ^@^Mustang Shocks & Struts^@^315.95^
@1296@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@1296@^http://www.steeda.com/qa1-96-04-mustang-k-member-338-mu1tk/^@^Steeda^@^QA1 Mustang Tubular K-Member (96-04)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/2/338-mu1tk.jpg^@^338-MU1TK^@^<p>QA1's tubular K-members are designed from the ground up for weight savings improved geometry and as a bolt-in swap for the factory K-member in race applications. May alter wheel base and stance.<br /> <br /> <strong>Bolt-In Design</strong> All mounting points have been digitally indexed from new factory K-members.<br /> <br /> <strong>Weight Savings</strong> Up to 28 lbs. lighter than the factory K-members with increased strength by design.<br /> <br /> <strong>Increased Header Clearance</strong> Header and oil pan clearance maximized for easier maintenance and installation.<br /> <br /> <strong>Modular Design</strong> for Versatility Spring perches are removable for extra weight savings when using coil-over kits. Stock or aftermarket a-arms can be used.<br /> <br /> <strong>Improved Geometry</strong> Bump steer anti-dive and Ackerman angles have been improved for maximum performance. </p><p>Time to install: <strong>About 3 Hours</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Tech Recommended</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Basic Tools</span> </div> </div> <div style=with:100%

>As used on the 2013 Mustang Cobra Jet program</span></li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 4 Hours</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Tech Recommended</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Basic Tools</strong></p><p>Model year(s): <strong>2014 2013 2012 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005</strong></p><p>Model(s): <strong>5.0L Bullitt GT GT500 Boss</strong></p><p>Transmission(s): <strong>Manual Automatic</strong></p>^@^Mustang^@^ 5.0L Bullitt GT GT500 Boss ^@^Mustang Suspension^@^2014 2013 2012 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005 ^@^Mustang Springs^@^299.95^
@1386@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@1386@^http://www.steeda.com/ford-racing-mustang-cobra-jet-spring-kit-05-14-161-m-5300-q/^@^Steeda^@^Ford Racing Mustang Cobra Jet Spring Kit (05-14)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/530/detailed/5/Ford_Racing_Mustang_Cobra_Jet_Spring_Kit_(05-10)161-M-5300-Q.jpg^@^161-M-5300-Q^@^<p>Ford Racing Cobra Jet Drag Springs are precision engineered to provide maximum traction to the drive wheels for improved weight transfer to control axle torque. The results are lower 1/4-mile elapsed times (ET's). </p> <p>This set of four Ford Racing Cobra Jet Drag Racing Springs are designed specifically for use on the 2005 to 2014 Mustangs including the GT Bullitt Boss and Shelby GT500 Models. </p> <p><strong>Please Note: </strong>These Springs were designed for drag racing applications only. </p> <p><strong>Product Benefits</strong> </p> <ul> <li>Specifically designed for drag racing applications</li> <li>Original equipment on 2008 &quot;Cobra Jet&quot; race car</li> <li>Lowers 1/4-mile ET's</li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 4 Hours</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Tech Required</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Shop Tools</strong></p><p>Model year(s): <strong>2014 2013 2012 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005</strong></p><p>Model(s): <strong>Bullitt GT Boss</strong></p><p>Transmission(s): <strong>Manual Automatic</strong></p>^@^Mustang^@^ Bullitt GT Boss ^@^Mustang Suspension^@^2014 2013 2012 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005 ^@^Mustang Springs^@^125.95^
@1387@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@1387@^http://www.steeda.com/steeda-mustang-stop-the-hop-package-555-2004/^@^Steeda^@^Steeda Mustang Stop The Hop Package - Stock Ride Height - 05-10^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/1/555-2004.jpg; http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/3/555-2004-1.jpg; http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/3/555-2004-2.jpg^@^555-2004^@^<p>Got wheel hop on your S197 Mustang? Looking to get it under control without breaking the bank? Steeda's cost effective Stop The Hop Pack is for you! </p> <p>This package features Steeda's industry leading chrome moly alloy steel rear lower trailing arms with Steeda's tubular upper 3rd link. </p> <p>Unlike competitive pieces which are made from standard mild steel Steeda uses chrome moly alloy steel which is twice as strong and lighter. The best of both worlds! </p> <p>This kit will get your axle hop under control improve straight line traction and corner exit. The result is faster 1/4 mile times and lower lap times at the road course all for a great price! </p> <p><strong>Package Includes</strong> </p> <ul> <li><strong>555-4422</strong> - Steeda Ultra-Strong Chrome Moly Control Arms</li> <li><strong>555-4097</strong> - Steeda Fixed Upper Third Link</li> </ul> <p><strong>Product Benefits</strong> </p> <ul> <li>Tame your Mustang's wheel hop</li> <li>Better handling with more stable cornering</li> <li>Great ride quality</li> <li>Great value w/ ultimate performance</li> <li>More Traction which means lower 60 fts!</li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 3 1/2 Hours</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Tech Recommended</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Basic Tools</strong></p><p>Model year(s): <strong>2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005</strong></p><p>Model(s): <strong>Bullitt GT V6 GT500</strong></p><p>Transmission(s): <strong>Manual Automatic</strong></p>^@^Mustang^@^ Bullitt GT V6 GT500 ^@^Mustang Suspension^@^2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005 ^@^Mustang Suspension Packages^@^349.95^
@1389@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@1389@^http://www.steeda.com/ford-racing-mustang-gt-coupe-assembled-handling-pack-05-14-161-fr3a-mgta/^@^Steeda^@^Ford Racing Mustang GT Coupe Assembled Handling Pack (05-14)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/6/ford-racing-mustang-gt-coupe-assembled-handling-pack-05-14-161-fr3a-mgta-2.JPG^@^161-M-FR1-MGT1^@^<p>Ford Racing's assembled handling pack includes pre-assembled struts. No spring compressor required strut/spring assembly is ready to bolt-in! Put a little &quot;road race&quot; into your Mustang GT with Ford Racing's handling pack. It's tuned to deliver improved handling without sacrificing ride quality. </p> <p><strong>Product Benefits</strong> </p> <ul> <li>Lowers car approximately 1.0&quot;</li> <li>All components are designed to work together as a package</li> <li>Includes all factory required one-time use fasteners</li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 6 1/2 Hours</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Tech Recommended</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Basic Tools</span> </div> </div> <div style=with:100%

