@1421@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@1421@^http://www.steeda.com/steeda-heavy-duty-mustang-panhard-bar-brace-555-2555/^@^Steeda^@^Steeda Heavy Duty Mustang Panhard Bar Brace (05-14)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/1/555-2555.jpg; http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/7/555-2555-1.jpg; http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/7/555-2555-2.jpg^@^555-2555^@^<p>Our Panhard brace stiffens the panhard bar mounting bracket which is prone to under load during cornering and provides some extra chassis rigidity as well. </p> <p>Not sure if you need to replace the factory panhard bar brace? Put your car in the air and grab the factory brace and pull on it. You will be able to flex it by hand! </p> <p>Like our panhard bar our panhard bar brace is made of super strong 4130 chrome moly alloy steel for the ultimate in strength! </p> <p><strong>Product Benefits</strong> </p> <ul> <li><strong>Competition tested and proven!</strong></li> <li>High quality construction</li> <li>Stiffens chassis </li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 1 Hour</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Easy</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Basic Tools</strong></p><p>Model year(s): <strong>2014 2013 2012 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005</strong></p><p>Model(s): <strong>Bullitt GT V6 GT500 Boss</strong></p><p>Transmission(s): <strong>Manual Automatic</strong></p>^@^Mustang^@^ Bullitt GT V6 GT500 Boss ^@^Mustang Chassis^@^2014 2013 2012 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005 ^@^Mustang Panhard Bars^@^124.95^
@1422@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@1422@^http://www.steeda.com/ford-racing-fr500c-mustang-tie-rod-end-05-10-161-m-3130-r2/^@^Steeda^@^Ford Racing FR500C Mustang Tie Rod End (05-10)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/530/detailed/5/ford-racing-fr500c-mustang-tie-rod-end-05-10-161-m-3130-r2.jpg^@^161-M-3130-R2^@^<p>Tie Rod Ends for your Mustang FR500C Race Car are available from Ford Racing. These track-use-only replacements have the extended stud for proper bump steer. They're also grease-able and include high-temperature dust boots. Sold individually. </p> <p><strong>Note: </strong> Sold individually. </p> <p><strong>Product Benefits</strong> </p> <ul> <li>Service replacement tie rod end for the Mustang FR500C race car</li> <li>Extended stud for proper bump steer</li> <li>Greaseable with high temp dust boot</li> <li>For track use only</li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 30 Minutes</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Tech Recommended</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Basic Tools</strong></p><p>Model year(s): <strong>2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005</strong></p><p>Model(s): <strong>All</strong></p><p>Transmission(s): <strong>Manual Automatic</strong></p>^@^Mustang^@^ All ^@^Mustang Steering^@^2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005 ^@^Mustang Bumpsteer^@^179.95^
@1423@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@1423@^http://www.steeda.com/steeda-x5-mustang-ball-joints-555-8108/^@^Steeda^@^Steeda X5 Mustang Ball Joints (05-10)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/1/555-8108.jpg^@^555-8108^@^<p>Steeda's X5 balljoints are designed to raise the roll center of your S197 Mustang which becomes lower as a result of lowering with lowering springs. </p> <p>Raising the roll center eliminates the issues associated with the lower roll center making for a great improvement in handling by reducing body roll and improving the front tire contact patch without increasing spring rate or roll bar rate. </p> <p>Steeda balljoints are made in the USA by a respected name-brand supplier to Ford GM and Daimler Chrysler. Except for their custom length they are the same materials and construction that has been extensively tested in Panther applications that is police cars and other severe duty applications where they have demonstrated durability that exceeds current production &quot;regular&quot; balljoints. They meet Ford's standards for friction wear and durability. </p> <p>Steeda's X5 ball joints change the bump steer geometry. Steeda highly recommends a bump steer kit be used in conjunction with the X5 balljoints. </p> <p><strong><span class=BodyBoldBlue">Please Note:</span></strong> 18&quot

