@1941@^GAS - Steeda^@^GAS - Steeda^@1941@^http://www.steeda.com/ford-racing-mustang-gt-x-pipe-05-10-161-m-5251-r/^@^Steeda^@^Ford Racing Mustang GT X-Pipe (05-10)^@^http://www.steeda.com/images/thumbnails/530/362/detailed/6/ford-racing-mustang-gt-x-pipe-05-10-161-m-5251-r.jpg^@^161-M-5251-R^@^<p>This Ford Racing Mustang GT X-pipe is designed to balance out the exhaust gas pressure in your system and will help improve exhaust flow for more power and sound. </p> <p>The installation of the Ford Racing X-pipe requires cutting and removing the stock H-pipe and reuses the factory catalytic converters saving you money. Clamps and instructions are provided. </p> <p>Constructed from sturdy 2.5&quot; mandrel bent T-409 Stainless Steel tubing the Clamp On X-Pipe will improve exhaust flow and last a lifetime. </p> <p><strong>Warning:</strong> This part has been designed and is intended for off-road application only. Installation of this part on a vehicle that is driven on public roads may violate U.S. and Canadian laws and regulations. </p> <p><strong>Product Benefits</strong> </p> <ul> <li>Clamp on installation - does not require welding! </li> <li>Converts your factory H-pipe to a more efficient X-pipe </li> <li>409 stainless steel X-pipe</li> </ul><p>Time to install: <strong>About 1 1/2 Hours</strong></p><p>Level of difficulty: <strong>Tech Recommended</strong></p><p>Tools needed: <strong>Basic Tools</strong></p><p>Model year(s): <strong>2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005</strong></p><p>Model(s): <strong>GT</strong></p><p>Transmission(s): <strong>Manual Automatic</strong></p>^@^Mustang^@^ GT ^@^Mustang Exhaust^@^2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005 ^@^Mustang X-Pipes^@^209.95^
